<br>
Good... Evil.. Neutral are all terms placed on those that need justification for their actions.  They do not exist save in the feeble minds of those too short sighted to see the truth of the matter.<br>
<br>
Enemies and allies, that is what truly is important.  Focus on those and ignore the lables that you are given, remain true to Father Innoruuk and Mistress Saryrn(or Bertoxxolus, or Rallos,) kill all that oppose you... and it matters little if they call you a hero or a villian.<br>
<br>
Do the koda'dal I flay or the dwarves I dine on consider me a hero?<br>
<br>
What of the guards of Nerriak whom I tend to?<br>
<br>
It is all perspective, and truly it matters little.<br>
