<br>
Your mantra of your pale friends is quiet impressive, perhaps if you keep repeating that to yourself, it may even become true... or not.  You almost sound as if you are trying despratly to convince yourself.<br>
<br>
You speak as if you know me... let me assure you that you do not.  I do not surround myself with those too weak to live amongst the people they were born into.  Nor do I surrond myselves with snivling knights who strive for peace, yet train for war.<br>
<br>
As for driving others away... if it pathetic blue skins like you, that have the audacity to claim the same proud race as I, then I will take that as a compliment.  Those that gather to me are strong in will, faith and drive.  They fight for the city of their birth and their god.  You would perhaps learn a lesson from them, were you not so blinded by foolish aspirations of acceptance.  Some are strong enough to stand proud among their people...<br>
<br>
I will agree in one point though, perhaps you two should get together.  Not only will that making finding you both to stomp your disgraceful lives out of existance that much easier, but perhaps in your ineptitude you may fall on each other's swords.<br>
