Of what I said to Tunyric, it still holds true. I have no doubt that a war of untold scale will come washing over our lands. I just happend to change my views on it. Comes with life experiance. Now I stand only to defend my friends and family. Nothing else really matters. <br>
<br>
I no longer follow the path of the Crimson Tear though. I left the rank and file of Lust for Blood some time ago. Just to make myself into more of what you dislike, I now stand in defence of Kelethin and Felwithe. And yes, I am welcome there. By banker and merchants alike. I earned thier trust and thier respect, just as some Fier'Dal or Koada'Dal can do in Neriak, if they so desire. <br>
<br>
*stands and looks the cleric in the eye*<br>
<br>
I fight for what I hold dear. Family and friends. I follow the path of Quellious for my OWN inner peace, yet I hold no illusions to be some peace loving sissy. I fight and I fight well, ask those who have fallen under my sword. <br>
<br>
