<br>
If you were as world-wise as you claim to be, you would know something of the treacherous past of the Koda and Fier'dal, but of course, that would require that your precious comfort be breached.  You are disgustingly typical of many whelps spit forth from Nerriak these days.  Far to weak to live among their proper society, they turn to the lessers for comfort.  Oh yes, shouts of &quot;freedom&quot; &quot;individuality&quot; &quot;tolerance&quot; can be heard echoing in shrill pre-pubescent Tier'dal voices all across the land...  How all the little failures must look up to you!  You certainly are an apt example.<br>
<br>
As for conformists and my banner, as you have never had the stones to stand with your people, how exactly would you know?  If I wished the opinion of a traveling oddity, something that your palerot friends can parade around to show their own superiority and great &quot;tolerance&quot; then I would speak to you.  You're nothing more then a leashed exotic animal.  <br>
<br>
Your pathetic existance aside, you make the foolish mistake of assuming that one Will is one mind.  Innoruuk granted all Tier'dal freedom, freedom from the Koda'dal who sought to burn Caerthiel around us, and freedom from direct rulership by a God.  We are granted the will to make our own choices, as evidence in yours.  That is what makes that truly follow Him strong, they have chosen His path, not had it forced upon them.  You are a fool though if you believe your actions do not serve him still.  The very apperance of your blue skin sparks hatred in others, and Innoruuk smiles.<br>
<br>
You speak of your willingness to step forward and defend Nerriak?  I would cut that lying tongue from your mouth were you before me!  Your words of loyalty to Nerriak ring very hollow, when you make bed in the very midst of those who would burn her to the ground.  I have little doubt that if your pale friends told you that they were going to kill every Tier'dal, except yourself of course, that you wouldn't raise a hand to stop them.  I doubt the guards care one bit about what religion you practice, I think the fact that you bear the markings of a guild dedicated to our most hated enemies defense may be a bit more of a put off.  Oh my, but why ever should that matter?  Centuries of bloodshed and war are not oft soon forgoten... at least not by those who have the sense to know about them.  I would wager you know very little of the history of your pale friends or of your place of birth.  Such is typical of your kind.  Your ignorance allows you to do as you wish with no sense of guilt.  What a simple life.<br>
<br>
There in lies the root of the disease that is you.  Selfishness.  You may cloth it in any manner of swath that you wish, but at your core you care for little save yourself and your beliefs.  See your words... how you mock those that stand in defense of their home and birthright... how you call them &quot;conformists&quot; as if your actions are those of an &quot;individual&quot; and not a &quot;damn dirty traitor.&quot;  <br>
<br>
How little you truly know of Innoruuk.  It is very sad to see a Tier'dal speak like an outsider, your family should have raised you better, or at least sold you so that you would get a proper education.  If the Tier'dal were perfect agents of Hate, we would be raised on high to our Father's plane, where we could serve Him fully.  As I am sure you have battered your impotent sword against the mindicants of his Plane, you will see that there are some Tier'dal who have achieved such a state.<br>
<br>
However, our place is here on Norrath and Luclin.<br>
<br>
We are not perfect followers of Hate, even though so many strive for that.  We are, however, the hearlds of His will here.  Being that we are mortal and not divine, we are flawed.  We can not exist in &quot;perfect&quot; anything, be it Hate, War, Fear, or Disease.  Mortals are not made to sustain on a single such facet.<br>
<br>
I am a priest of Hate.  I hold the title of Regent amongst the proper church, and High Regent in Necropolis.  I do not Hate perfectly.  I am a mortal and flawed.<br>
<br>
You speak that as an insult?  It is merely a fact.  All mortal followers are flawed.  If they existed in perfect deferance to their God's Will, they would not be on this world.  Even so, I am a fine insturment of Innoruuk and Saryrn.  They have shown me their favor and in respect and repayment, I carry forth their Will on these worlds.<br>
<br>
Friends leave and families die, but faith exists forever.  When your friends turn their backs and your family passes away into nothing, what will you left with?<br>
<br>
Just a broken Ter'dal with a sword.  Freeport taverns are filled with your ilk.  Thankfully, your kind make excellent slave stock.<br>
<br>
I look forward to seeing your tired and broken face looking up at me from my pens.  I will save a special set of shackles just for you.<br>
<br>
Perhaps I should excellerate this process?  It would please me greatly to hear those that you hold dear scream out to Saryrn... It would please me greatly indeed.<br>
<br>
<br>
