&quot;Na' like a fookin' deathknight pretendin' ta be a friend'a good an' a servant'a th' Tranquil.  Feh.&quot;  Inhuman eyes look scornfully upon Zaith.  &quot;A deathknight's powers c'm on'y f'm th' dark gods.  Bertox.  In'ruk.  Cazic.  If ya was a straight fighta', like me, mebbe I could buy it.  Mebbe.  Bu' I ain't buyin' nothin' f'm no deathknight.&quot;<br>
<br>
She nods firmly to punctuate her statement and goes back to sharpening her blade. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
