</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tunyricllanower@firionavie>Tunyric Llanower</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ego Authority</span><br>  Posts: 237<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/30/03 11:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4677.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Double Standards</span><hr size=1> Vabris my actions were in direct retaliation in order to protect the innocent lives of my citizenry. Ill be the first to admit my guards are inept so the task of protection falls upon my shoulders and as for reanimation if my memory serves you fled once my former leader Frayzer came and asked you to. Taking orders from a Wood ef druid, How proud Innoruuk must be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khaylee>Khaylee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/30/03 12:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4677.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Honored Enemy</span><hr size=1> You have forgotten the Honored Enemy.<br>
<br>
Whether you follow your gods to the death in your &quot;evil&quot; or &quot;good&quot; ways or not, there is still such a thing as an HONORED ENEMY.<br>
<br>
/ooc An excellent example would be to take the Klingon approach to playing an &quot;evil&quot; race/class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaithfv>ZaithFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight of Quellious<br>
Rhymes with Faith...</span><br>  Posts: 245<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/30/03 1:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4677.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Double Standards</span><hr size=1> *gives a sigh and rolls his eyes*<br>
<br>
You dont know me that well either Vabris. When I get word that Neriak is under attack, say by the halflings, I come rushing to Her aid, despite the fact that my parents and my entire house was burnt to the ground by the Inner Guard for my fathers faith in Bristlebane. How tolerant our kind is. I suppose it didnt matter than my Mother was a High Priestess in the Church of Innoruuk, that didnt stop the guard from burning them alive. Yet, I still come to my cities aid if they are under attack. Alas, after slaying the guards that led the attack on my House, I am no longer welcome in my own home. I did not kill them because they were Tier'Dal, I killed them because they were murders and deserved death by my hand. Yet, I still stand on that bridge and do my duty as a Knight of Neriak, regardless if I am wished to be there or not. <br>
<br>
*his face grows abit cold*<br>
<br>
Make no mistake Vabris, my friends and my family will stand by my side as long as I take a breath and they will find those responsible for bringing me down. I was raised to follow the Father, I was raised to spill the blood of those who tried to destroy us, I was RAISED, dear Vabris, in the Halls of the Dead, the HEART of Innoruuks faithful. I know WELL and good about what Innoruuk wishs and what his will is. You do not need to give your speech of Innoruuks power and glory, I was raised listening to them!<br>
<br>
*The knight takes a breath*<br>
<br>
I welcome you to come for me Vabris. You will learn, as many others have, that I am not an easy target. Paladin or shadow knight, they have all fallen to me before. <br>
<br>
*grining, he looks at the frog*<br>
<br>
You really should keep a more open mind. Our powers, as any others who uses magic, come from with us. For others, it is easier to call upon a God so thier magic will come. The power I wield is mine and mine alone. Given to me by Innoruuk when my mother bore me and no one can take it away. <br>
<br>
*giving the little red thing a cold smile, he pats Tranquility's hilt*<br>
<br>
Why not come and have a go as well? You will see, just like Vabris will, that my power is mine alone and Quellious walks with me..<br>
<br>
